pugixml
------------------------------------------
pugixml is a light-weight C++ XML processing library. It features:

 - DOM-like interface with rich traversal/modification capabilities
 - Extremely fast non-validating XML parser which constructs the DOM tree from
   an XML file/buffer
 - XPath 1.0 implementation for complex data-driven tree queries
 - Full Unicode support with Unicode interface variants and automatic encoding
   conversions

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.13-1
  libgcc1-4.5.3-3
  libstdc++6-4.5.3-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.22.51-2
  cmake-2.8.4-1
  cygport-0.10.10-1
  gcc4-core-4.5.3-3
  gcc4-g++-4.5.3-3
  make-3.82.90-1

Canonical website:
  http://pugixml.org/

Canonical download:
  http://pugixml.googlecode.com/files/pugixml-1.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack pugixml-1.0-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./pugixml-1.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/pugixml-1.0-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/pugixml-1.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libpugixml1.0-1.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libpugixml-devel-1.0-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(pugixml)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/pugixml.README
  /usr/share/doc/pugixml/README.txt

(libpugixml1.0)
  /usr/bin/cygpugixml-1.0.dll

(libpugixml-devel)
  /usr/include/pugiconfig.hpp
  /usr/include/pugixml.hpp
  /usr/lib/libpugixml.dll.a
  /usr/share/pugixml/contrib/foreach.hpp

------------------

